               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1330" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1330" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1330" type="surname" value="SOLOMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1330" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>ABRAHAM SOLOMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a furniture-broker, and live in Little Queen-street. The prisoner was a French-polisher, and was at my house on the 31st of March—he left that evening, and did not return the next morning as he ought—I lost the cream-ewer on the 31st, and the other property prior to that time—I had used the ewer that day at breakfast—this is it—it has a crest on one side, and initials on the other—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1331" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1331" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1331" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1331" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN DAVIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with Mr. Wells in Queen-street. About ten o'clock that night, the prisoner came to the George public-house—I saw him with the milk jug—I heard Mr. Soloman had lost one, and gave Information.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-1332" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1332" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1332" type="surname" value="PEARCE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-1332" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD PEARCE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am potman at the George. The prisoner came on the evening of the 31st of March, into the tap-room, sat down, and threw down some bed-furniture, and in about ten minutes after, he said, "I have</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184004060193"></xptr>
               <p>got something at the next house, which I want to get away, I got it from a sale"—he went and got a milk-ewer like this.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I could not return, as the officer took me, and the bed-tick does not belong to Mr. Soloman.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
